From the point of international trade, the virus cost the world economy about US$2.5 trillion.In politics, it was the year of ‘Trump Trouble’ for democracy.  It goes without saying that 2020 is the worst year for most of us. Annus horribilis, a terrible year.
A lot of tragedies keep us staring at screens, newspapers and radios. With the Covid-19 pandemic, economic collapse, unemployment, heavy debt and a surge in insecurity, many Kenyans will be happy to see the end of 2020.



