Also, Kenya was elected a non-permanent member of the UN Security Council, defeating Djibouti for a seat designated for African countries in June, a good thing for the nation. After all, it was not many years in history that a pandemic sparked terror worldwide. 
Big or small, poor or wealthy, white, black or brown, the pandemic doesn’t discriminate. The truth is that the virus seems to have deliberately shown its more horrible form to developed and powerful countries.
The United States, India, Brazil, Russia, France, the United Kingdom, and Italy have excellent economies and health infrastructure but suffered heavily. 





International trade
More than 80 million people in the world have been infected. From the point of international trade, the virus cost the world economy about US$2.5 trillion.
As in the 1990s, it has been argued many times in favour of globalisation that it will bring the world closer in the face of a deep global crisis.
Different countries will give up small personal interests, and the whole world will stand together against the pandemic. But with Covid-19, we saw all countries close their borders to the rest of the world.
In politics, it was the year of ‘Trump Trouble’ for democracy. In the US presidential election, Trump’s defeat was not an explosion, as it seemed to be written on the wall several months ago.



